news.title: China: Longfor Group Holdings' vice chairman resigns
news.para: The resignation follows former chairwoman, Wu Yajun, who stepped down in October and was replaced by Chen Xuping, 40, the company's chief executive.

news.title: Coal India subsidiary NCL to start M-Sand production
news.para: M-Sand is artificial sand produced from crushing hard stones into small sand-sized angular shaped particles, washed and finely graded to be used as construction aggregate. It is an alternative to river sand for construction works.

news.title: Building material segments to grow 8-12% for the next 4-5 years: HDFC Securities
news.para: As per the industry estimates, 38% of the Indian population would occupy Indian cities by 2025 versus 33% currently. By 2030, 80% of the Indian population would be classified as middle class, against 50% currently.

news.title: Chennai development body to create growth cluster at Madambakkam
news.para: Governor R N Ravi, while making his customary address to the assembly, said land would be pooled with the consent of landowners and classified based on their use to promote planned development, while ensuring that the benefits of development are shared with the land owners.

news.title: Proposal to make it must to pool land beyond 70% limit in Delhi
news.para: he housing and urban affairs ministry has moved a Cabinet proposal for mandatory inclusion of land under the Land Pooling policy in sectors where 70% or more land has been pooled.

news.title: Brick&Bolt raises $10 million from Accel and Celesta Capital
news.para: Brick&Bolt plans to use the funding to enhance its tech stack, strengthen its leadership team and expand to 12+ cities in the next 15 months. Cilix Capital, an international investment-banking firm, has advised the Series A2 round.

news.title: Generate your own funds, Gujarat CM tells urban bodies
news.para: Patel convened a meeting of elected leaders of municipal corporations, municipalities and urban development authorities in Gandhinagar recently, and said that the system of the state government and Union government providing grants will gradually be phased out.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 13,000 properties under tax net
news.para: “While 4,500 new properties brought under tax net were from Panchavati division, around 3,500 properties were from Cidco division,” said the official.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's rebate plan fails, only 40% pay property tax
news.para: The civic body’s data shows total demand of property tax increased to Rs950 crore in current financial year due to revaluation and reassessment drive carried out in last few years.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property to be demolished if regularization plea rejected
news.para: The Gujarat government passed a bill in December seeking to regularize unauthorized constructions in urban areas by collecting impact fees from owners. However, the Ahmedabad civic body has received only 4,048 applications so far.

news.title: Worli BDD buildings to be ready by December 2024: Mhada
news.para: “Work is also being expedited at N M Joshi Marg and Naigaum, Dadar. Now, there are no major hurdles with regard to tenants and residents of these chawls ,” he said.

news.title: NCLT okays Adani Good Homes' sole bid for Radius Estates
news.para: ICICI Prudential Venture Capital Fund and Beacon Trusteeship, who are creditors of the company and held its debentures on behalf of investors, had opposed Adani's bid for the real estate company citing foul play. They had demanded that the insolvency process be scrapped and started afresh.

news.title: HDFC, India Overseas Bank hike lending rate by up to 25 basis points
news.para: According to the HDFC Bank website, the overnight MCLR is now 8.50 per cent from earlier 8.30 per cent, an increase of 20 basis points, while the MCLR for one month is 8.55 per cent up from 8.30 per cent, a rise of 25 basis points.

news.title: Financing for Chinese real estate firms jumps 33% year-on-year in Dec 2022
news.para: The central bank said on Thursday that for cities where the selling prices of new homes fall month-on-month and year-on-year for three consecutive months, the floor on mortgage rates can be lowered or abolished for first-time home buyers in phases.

news.title: HDFC Capital raises $376 million for affordable housing fund
news.para: The latest fund raising is the third by HDFC Capital's affordable real estate fund (H-Care 3) and the primary investor in the H-Care schemes is a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Abu Dhabi Investment Authority (ADIA), HDFC said in a statement.
